For me personally, the number one metric is based on my happiness. And happiness here does not necessarily always mean pleasure or joy as I am doing it... I would imagine my future self reflecting on the decision that I am about to make, and see if I would be proud of feel a sense of contentment that I made the decision to do whatever I am about to do.

P.S. If you want to see the full interview, then go to @startcanadapodcast 👈 for the link.

node.text:
Do you you agree?👀 Your social media's feed says more about you then what's currently happening in the world. Part of the reason why you keep seeing negative news on your feed is because you keep interacting with those type of content. And the algorithm takes note of your behavior to keep feeding you content that you are likely to interact with...

Anyway, this is a snippet of an hour long interview I did with @startcanadapodcast 2 weeks ago where we talked about social media marketing for entrepreneurs.

Go check out their page @startcanadapodcast 👈to see the full episode if you want some free tips on growing your business utilizing social media as a tool. 📲

node.title: @iamdaviddang - Social media is just exposing us🙈

No money needed, no special experience, just 5 days (90 minutes a day) and a simple commitment…

👉 Go to the link in my bio @iamdaviddang to register for this FREE event now!🔥

⁣
If you want to make 2021 your best year ever, then read this short caption for 1 minute.. ⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣
⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣
Do you feel that social media drains your energy?⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣
⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣
 Every single day the average person spends 90 minutes on social media.⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣
⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣
For most people, social media feels like a time-waster, mindless scrolling & negative content that is not truly beneficial for their lives.⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣
⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣
Eventually, they feel like those platforms reduce their dreams and limit their potential.⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣
⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣
If you resonate with these feelings, you should know that social media can be a powerful tool for consuming valuable content to learn new skills & increase your income.⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣
⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣
To make this change, all you have to do is follow the right people so you can grow your mindset instead of limiting your purpose.⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣
⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣
That's why I highly recommend you to follow the account in the list down below:⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣

node.text:
According to theory we are either left-brain or right-brain dominant.

“If you’re mostly analytical and methodical in your thinking, you’re said to be left-brained. If you tend to be more creative or artistic, you’re thought to be right-brained.

The left brain is more verbal, analytical, and orderly than the right brain. It’s sometimes called the digital brain. It’s better at things like reading, writing, and computations.

According to dated research, the left brain is also connected to:

logic
sequencing
linear thinking
mathematics
facts
thinking in words

The right brain is more visual and intuitive. It’s sometimes referred to as the analog brain. It has a more creative and less organized way of thinking.

Dated research suggests the right brain is also connected to:

imagination
holistic thinking
intuition
arts
rhythm
nonverbal cues
feelings visualization
daydreaming”

Which one are you?🤔 Comment below 👇👇

📷 @MotivationMafia

When you push yourself beyond limits, you discover inner reserves, which you never thought existed earlier.⁣⁣

People often fail to take action and create a better future for themselves because they're too focused on unimportant things.  ⁣⁣⁣⁣

Instead of learning how to REALLY make a difference in their lives, they procrastinate - as most people do.⁣⁣⁣⁣
⁣⁣⁣⁣
The thing is... If hard work alone had helped to create success and wealth, everyone hardworking the 9-5 would have been a millionaire by now. ⁣⁣⁣⁣

There's a specific reason why out of 330 million people in the US, there are only 788 billionaires... ⁣⁣⁣⁣
